author: ryan86
message:
Import/Export Reference Data (#1094)

* First cut at exporting reference data to arches json format.

* Change format of reference data in arches json. Fix tests.

* Add threat type authority document to repo. Adjust tests.

* Concept export and refactor export_json command.

* Remove export_graphs command. Use python manage.py packages -o export_json -g 'graphids or "all" or "branches" or "resources"' instead.

* Refactor import cli.

* Create concept collections on reference data import from arches.json.

* Add indexing to arches json reference data import. Refactor reference data import. Add test reference data to repo as arches json. Add unique constraint to concept relations table. Adjust tests.

* Fix concept_import_test so that concepts are now indexed after term index is created.

author: robgaston
message:
better workaround for chosen binding issue
computed for options list and for value were conflicting,
causing the widget id to update when changing between selections.

was working around this with a flag in JS, but it is better handled
by wrapping the view content containing the chosen dropdown in an 'if'
and setting the widget reference on the view model to null before updating,
which forces the DOM around the chosen dropdown to be refreshed every time the
selection changes.

re: #626

Bring in line with Geom Widget Branch (#835)

* stubbing out initial pages for editing and managing resource instances, re #768, re #786, re #765

* move loading-mask element into base.htm

* keep moving resource management and editor pages forward, re #768, re #786, re #765

* rename BaseNiftyView to BaseManagerView

* Added geometry widget js file

* added docs for radio-boolean and made the radio boolean widget the default for boolen datatypes

* adding support for form delete feature
re: #810

* Add check for d_data_type value in nodes table. (#811)

* improving manager back buttons

* only showing "back to cards" for resources

* #723 Added geometry template and css. Added a basic map to the widget

* add base-manager.js view to go along with the base-manager.htm template, re #765

* update graph.js view to use the new base-manager view, re #765

* stub out empty resource view, re #765

* don't display loading mask by default, re #765

* fix broken build

* need to use a KO click handler to allow a user to click on a link in the side nav when the nav item has a sub-menu, re #765

* remove teset code, re #765

* move resources and graphs computed observables up to base-manager.js, re #765

* improve page navigation, re #765

* add trans tags

* add tile/card view for resource type selector, #768

* transitions working for all elements in map controls toolbar, re #723

* improved map controls animation timing

* added active button highlighting and panel switching in map controls. Worked on default zoom and center point configs

* separated map center into two properties centerX and centerY, re #723

* Added subtitle to configuration form, re #725

* added config fields for center x, center y and geocoder

* added binding handler for jquery animations in map controls, re #723

* switched openlayers map for mapbox-gl, re #723

author: chiatt
message: changed basemap_layers model to map_layers and changed the name of the layer column in basemap_layers to 'layerdefinitions'. The layerdefinitions column stores an array of layers rather than single layer per layer record. This allows support for combining layers to be managed as single overlay within a map - particularly useful when an overlay has different geom types. Updated the mapbox bindings and geometry widget to support these changes, re #723

author: veuncent
message:
1650 docker support (#2530)

* Add initial draft for Dockerfile and accompanying files, re #1650

* Only run collectstatic in PROD, allways run tests, re #1650

* Add site-packages to STATICFILES_DIRS as quick fix for bower_components not being found in site-packages dir, re#1650

* Remove Nginx from docker-compose line-up for now, re#1650

* Rename service and volume names, re #1650

* Change Postgres version from 9.5 to 9.6

* Remove unncessesary pip installs, re #1650

* Remove unncessesary installation of Mapnik and dependencies, re #1650

* Change Elasticsearch version from 5.2.1 -> 5.2, re#1650

* Add verbosity to init script to alert user database is being dropped.
Add quotes to echo commands, fix not all messages showing during script.
Change tab to spaces in Readme.md, re #1650

* Re-add apt-get and pip dependencies removed earlier, as it was breaking the build, re #1650

* Some Readme cleanup, re #1650

* Move database initialization to entrypoint. Only run if db does not exist yet. re #1650

* Add Elasticsearch port as env variable, re #1650

* Move setup.py develop to entrypoint, so it is only fired when DJANGO_MODE = DEV, re #1650

* Change default dir to arches root.
Add Docker cleanup script.
re #1650

* Add cleanup script to Readme, re #1650

* Add SPARQLWrapper to pip install, re#1650

* Set existing Elasticsearch port with env variable that confirms to format of other env variables in Dockerfile/docker-compose.yml. Reason: ELASTICSEARCH_HTTP_PORT is also used in other places. re #1650

* Remove LetsEncrypt from docker-compose.yml for now. Also remove references to unused services in Readme.md. re #1650

* Explain EC2_PRIVATE_IP setting, re #1650

* Remove dropdowns.rdf reference, re #1650

* Rename install folder, move stuff to /tmp

* Rename install folder, part II, remove SPARQLWrapper from explicit pip install (installed through requirements.txt), re #1650

* Remove volume for ENV folder, as this prevents any packages to by installed there on image build time (these installs are hidden by overlaid volume on run time), re #1650

* Add env variable for Elasticsearch, re #1650

* Add env variable used to create custom Arches project.
Add command to init custom Arches project.
Add command to set correct workdir. Re #1650

* Update Readme to include workflow of setting up a custom Arches project.
Major refactoring of Readme.
Add safety check in entrypoint when creating custom Arches project. Re #1650

* Remove installing defaultgraphs and concepts, re #1650

* Rename env variable CUSTOM_ARCHES_PROJECTS.
Remove support for multiple custom apps.
Move settings_local from core Arches to custom Arches app on init.
Remove STATICFILES_DIR setting from settings_local.py, was causing trouble due to import order.
Set correct workdir for all commands.
Refactor Readme file: parameter list.
Remove unused volumes from docker-compose.yml. Re #1650

* Fix path in entrypoint.sh.
Some Readme.md edits. re #1650

* Change move command into copy.
Edited Readme to correct path error.
Remove absolute paths from entrypoint. Re #1650

* Add custom scripts folder for users to expand on entrypoint.sh.
Rename PROJECT_ROOT env var to APP_FOLDER.
Simplified path in APP_FOLDER env variable.

* Revert "Add custom scripts folder for users to expand on entrypoint.sh."

This reverts commit 3ccf7dd4860f61eace96cb13b532b9b2bcc157a6.

* Add custom scripts folder for users to expand on entrypoint.sh.
Rename PROJECT_ROOT env var to APP_FOLDER.
Simplified path in APP_FOLDER env variable, re #1650

* Add support for (remote) debugging of docker container through ptvsd, re #1650

* Remove remote debugging commands from manage.py, accidentally checked this in, re #1650

* Add fix for dev environments where host source code is mounted into container and thus hides stuff installed during Docker image build, re #1650

* Add bower install to entrypoint.sh, re #1650

* Run unit tests only in DEV mode, re #1650

* Add unneccessary stuff to .dockerignore, re #1650

* Add migrations on startup.
Add Django port as optional env variable.
Some entrypoint.sh cleanup.
Edit Readme.

* Fix variable brackets, re #1650

* Remove http: from URLs, re #2037

* Remove `bower install` from Dockerfile build. This should be run in entrypoint to avoid duplicates.

* Add bower_components to .dockerignore, re #1650

* Add option to set SECRET_KEY in settings.py (for running Arches without custom app), re #1650

* Improve the way entrypoint checks if database already exists, re #1650

* Add fail when unit tests fail.
Allow executable permission on test files, re #1650

* Create a simple first run setup:
Make docker-compose.yml ready for running without editing first.
Edit Readme to reflect this.
Add some verbosity to entrypoint.
Make Mapbox API env variable optional.

* Add installation of default grapgs and concepts on startup, re #1650

* Fix Readme indendation, re #1650

* Format docker/Readme.me, re #1650

* Add Docker commands to allow for e.g. running of tests or clearing the db.
Delete duplicate function, re #1650

* Change cli command `setup` into `setup_db`.
Temporarily add indexing of ES after running setup_db.
Add check if db server is up.

* Optimize container startup: re-run installation commands, which allows the user to mount volumes on ENV/lib and bower_components folders.
Some organization/cleanup of entrypoint.sh.
Add missing (optional) env variable to docker-compose.yml, re #1650

* Move all online/download commands from entrypoint to docker build, re #1650

* Fix typo in Docker Readme, re #1650

* Remove MAPBOX_API_KEY settings, as this has been moved to System Settings.
Remove AWS-specific settings, re #1650

* Remove entrypoint commands that require internet access. All these have been moved to the Dockerfile (see [5e2ddd2]).
Remove obsolete virtualenv volume, re #1650

* Re-add `bower install` to entrypoint. This was necessary, as the bower_components folder may be overwritten by user during runtime.
Move function to more appropriate position in file, re #1650

* Remove FORCE_DB_INIT env variable, as it has been replaced by the setup_db command

* Remove obsolete delete_indexes and setup_indexes commands from entrypoint, re #1650

* Edited Readme to reflect feedback from mradamcox.
Add some verbosity to entrypoint.sh (minor), re #1650

* Add postgres port to Docker entrypoint to allow running PostgreSQL on another port than 5432, re #1650

* Add run_migrations command. Move folder commands to relevant functions to make sure those functions are ran from the correct folder, re #1650

* Update dock repo name after renaming organization from arches -> archesproject, re #1650

* Update Docker organization name, re #1650

* Remove run_tests command from docker-compose.yml, re #1650

* Adjust Readme to reflect that docker-compose.yml can be used for production environments.
Move some sections to a Misc / Good-to-Know, re #1650

* Add Nginx and LetsEncrypt services to docker-compose.yml.
Add STATIC_ROOT setting to allow for production mode and collectstatic command to work, re #1650

* Fix bug in entrypoint (;;), re #1650

* Re-enable protocol in aat provider endpoint, re #1650

* Remove geocoders.py, which was deleted from master branch, re #1650

* Remove build directions for Nginx service from docker-compose.yml.
Add some production settings explanations and a troubleshoot section, re #1650

* PART II: Remove build directions for Nginx service from docker-compose.yml.
Add some production settings explanations and a troubleshoot section, re #1650

* Remove irrelevant label for LetsEncrypt service in docker-compose.yml

* Update Arches installation process in Dockerfile, re #1650

* Fix dupliacted volume declarations, re #1650

* Add installing from requirements.txt file, re #1650

* Create compose file for automating unit tests. This causes Docker Cloud to run tests after a successful build, re #1650

* Fix LetsEncrypt docker volumes, re #1650

* Remove es index_database from entrypoint, re #1650

* Remove pip package ptvsd from installation (used for debugging from Visual Studio (Code), so too case specific for main Arches Docker image, re #1650

* Remove container name from docker-compose-test.yml, re #1650

Fix race condition when saving cards in graph designer #9858

The frontend saves cards twice, once to update the card tree,
and once to update the permissions tree. If two requests are
pending, and both requests "think" a new CardXNodeXWidget
must be created, the second will fail with an IntegrityError.
